To compile the tool, the best way is to use nix

Start doing

> nix-shell
> make 

Then you can start using it iteractively by doing 
./maskverif 
or by passing a .mv file
./maskverif < tutorial.mv

A small tutorial is provide in tutorial.mv


Alternatively, you can install maskverif as a library for ocamlfind via
make install

To make maskverif available as an opam executable in your path run
opam pin add .
opam install maskverif

Run eval "$(opam env)", to update your path according

To remove the executable, including libraries
opam remove maskverif